---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith('/')
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
---

<BaseLayout title="Things to Do — Ramey & Hiba">
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">The Ancient Medina</h2>
    <img
      class="attraction-image"
      src={`${base}images/Medina_Isolated.png`}
      alt="Illustration of an arched doorway in the Rabat medina, with lanterns, plants, and a minaret in the distance"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <div class="section-body">
      <p>
        Rabat&rsquo;s historic medina invites you into the rhythm and texture of authentic
        Moroccan life. Winding through a labyrinth of covered souks and open-air stalls,
        visitors discover an abundance of handcrafted goods &mdash; embroidered textiles,
        hand-painted ceramics, aromatic spices, and ornate lanterns. Whether seeking a memento
        of Morocco or simply wishing to absorb the color and energy of a living marketplace,
        the medina is an experience that lingers long after you depart.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--narrow">
    <h2 class="section-title">Chellah Castle</h2>
    <div class="section-meta">
      <p class="section-meta__line">254H+HVC، محمد السادس، الرباط، Morocco</p>
      <p class="section-meta__line">06 93 24 18 56</p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p>
        Nestled within ancient walls draped in bougainvillea, the Chellah is one of Morocco&rsquo;s
        most hauntingly beautiful historical sites. This walled necropolis encompasses Roman
        ruins dating to the first century alongside a medieval Islamic sanctuary, where minarets
        rise above lush, overgrown gardens and resident white storks keep a silent watch. A walk
        through the Chellah is a walk through centuries.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--narrow">
    <h2 class="section-title">Kasbah Oudaya</h2>
    <div class="section-meta">
      <p class="section-meta__line">25J7+PGX, Rabat, Morocco</p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p>
        Perched dramatically at the confluence of the Bou Regreg River and the Atlantic Ocean,
        the Kasbah of the Udayas is among Rabat&rsquo;s most cherished treasures. Its narrow lanes,
        whitewashed walls trimmed in cobalt blue, and fragrant Andalusian gardens evoke a timeless
        elegance. Wander through its winding streets to the clifftop terrace, where sweeping views
        of the ocean and the city of Sal&eacute; unfold before you in every direction.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--narrow">
    <h2 class="section-title">La Marina Sal&eacute;</h2>
    <div class="section-meta">
      <p class="section-meta__line">25HG+RP9, Sal&eacute;, Morocco</p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p>
        For those drawn to the water, the Sal&eacute; Marina presents a spectacular vantage point
        from which to experience Rabat&rsquo;s coastal beauty. Embark on a scenic boat tour along
        the Bou Regreg River, gliding past the medina walls and the Kasbah of the Udayas as the
        Atlantic horizon stretches beyond. For the more adventurous, jet skiing offers an
        exhilarating rush on the open water &mdash; a thrilling contrast to the city&rsquo;s
        ancient calm.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
